    <main>
        <section class="note-section">
            <h2>GDPR Basics</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Notification of data breach must be made within 72 hours.</li>
                <li><strong>Data Processor:</strong> Processes personal data solely on behalf of the data controller.</li>
                <li><strong>Data Controller:</strong> Controls the processing of data.</li>
                <li><strong>Data Transfer:</strong> GDPR restricts data transfers to countries outside the EU.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="note-section">
            <h2>Reducing GDPR Exposure</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Anonymization:</strong> Removes all relevant data so that the original subject cannot be identified.</li>
                <li><strong>Pseudonymization:</strong> Uses pseudonyms to represent other data, resulting in fewer GDPR requirements.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="note-section">
            <h2>Data Lifecycle</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Create</li>
                <li>Store</li>
                <li>Use</li>
                <li>Share</li>
                <li>Archive</li>
                <li>Destroy</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="note-section">
            <h2>Data Security Controls</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Marking, Labeling, Handling, Classification</li>
                <li>Data Handling</li>
                <li>Data Destruction</li>
                <li>Record Retention</li>
                <li>Tape Backup Security</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>

